# Dairo + Hono

This starter was scaffolded by `dairo init hono`. It includes a Hono app with an
outbound send route and an inbound webhook handler that verifies delivery
signatures. It runs on Workers, Bun, and Node.

## Files

- `src/index.ts` — the Hono app: `POST /api/dairo/send` and the inbound webhook
  handler at `POST {{inbox_route}}`.

## 1. Set your API key

```sh
cp .env.example .env
```

```text
DAIRO_API_KEY=dairo_...
DAIRO_WEBHOOK_SECRET=whsec_...
```

On Cloudflare Workers, set these as Worker secrets and bindings instead of `.env`.

## 2. Install and run

```sh
{{install_cmd}}
```

Run with your preferred Hono adapter (Node, Bun, or `wrangler dev` for Workers).

## 3. Register the webhook

```sh
dairo webhook create --url https://<your-host>{{inbox_route}} --event {{webhook_event}}
```

Local development:

```sh
dairo listen --forward-to http://localhost:3000{{inbox_route}}
```

## Raw body gotcha

`c.req.text()` returns the **raw request body** — verify against those exact
bytes before parsing JSON. `verifyWebhookRequest` is async/Web-Crypto-capable so
it works in edge runtimes without Node polyfills.
